Reasoning: The paper discusses the value of Dimensions as a scholarly database for impact assessment, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on a new scholarly database. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also relevant as the paper discusses citation counts and their correlation between different databases. cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper touches on research evaluations and their impact. cs.DB (Databases) is also a possible category as the paper compares Dimensions to Scopus and the Web of Science, which are both databases.
